doc.after: Immigration has been a major source of population growth and cultural change throughout much of the history of Sweden and in recent centuries the country has been transformed from a nation of net emigration ending after World War I to a nation of net immigration from World War II onwards The economic social and political aspects of immigration have caused controversy regarding ethnicity economic benefits jobs for non immigrants settlement patterns impact on upward social mobility crime and voting behaviour 228
